div.p:
There was a dissentyon betwene Paule and Barnabas for Ihō whose sirname was Marke, whome Paule woulde not receyue, because he wente


from thē, but Barnabas toke Marke wyth hym,
                  Actes. 15. and so they departed a sunder one from the other. Where by shoulde haue folowed, as it was thoughte, some greate rebuke and shame. But God disposing the matter, there ensued greate frute and profite. For the worde of God was opened & preached to manye.
